Jamie Carragher on Emery: &ldquo;I said it before, I don&rsquo;t see anything different to when Ars&egrave;ne Wenger was there at the end, I don&rsquo;t see it. In fact, at times, it looks worse.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Carragher: &ldquo;I actually said Sheffield United tonight, in the first-half, played better football than Arsenal. You&rsquo;d never really say that under Ars&egrave;ne Wenger.&rdquo;

Emery: &quot;We did not deserve to lose &amp; we will think about where we can improve. When we were losing 1-0, we controlled the game but &amp; defended well but they had a lot of players in their box so it was difficult to achieve attacks&quot;<br />
<br />
Emery: &quot;We did not deserve to lose &amp; we conceded a lot of corners in the first half &amp; they scored in one action. Above all, we have to improve by not allowing balls like that. When we have our opportunities to attack, we created more chances than them but did not score today&quot;

